WEBVTT

00:08.322 --> 00:10.755
Where do they
all go, anyway?

00:10.757 --> 00:12.031
Who?

00:12.033 --> 00:13.667
People that live in
these neighborhoods.

00:13.669 --> 00:15.573
Money moves in,
they move out.

00:15.575 --> 00:17.040
The poor get pushed out,

00:17.042 --> 00:18.377
but murder gets
to stay, huh?

00:18.379 --> 00:20.210
Sounds about right.

00:20.212 --> 00:22.218
What do we got?

00:22.220 --> 00:23.555
We got a male, white.

00:23.557 --> 00:25.220
Counted a dozen
stab wounds.

00:25.222 --> 00:26.125
I.D.?

00:26.127 --> 00:27.526
No wallet, no
cell phone,

00:27.528 --> 00:28.632
but I'm pretty sure

00:28.634 --> 00:30.067
that's Brent Madison.

00:30.069 --> 00:31.267
What? You're kidding.

00:31.269 --> 00:32.869
Nope, the wife and I got
into farm-to-table cooking

00:32.871 --> 00:34.072
'cause of him.

00:34.074 --> 00:36.409
Well, he was a chef
on a reality cooking show

00:36.411 --> 00:37.745
a couple
of seasons back.

00:37.747 --> 00:39.018
He won big.

00:39.020 --> 00:41.882
He opened up a place
in Tribeca, the LES.

00:41.884 --> 00:44.187
Yeah, that's him
all right.

00:44.189 --> 00:46.091
No cash register to rob,
no knife,

00:46.093 --> 00:47.427
no footprints in the blood.

00:47.429 --> 00:48.763
May be a hit.

00:48.765 --> 00:50.259
I may have a suspect for you.

00:50.261 --> 00:51.995
Last week, my partner
and I responded

00:51.997 --> 00:53.397
to a call here.

00:53.399 --> 00:56.101
Two males having a verbal altercation.
Huh.

00:56.103 --> 00:57.901
It was the victim
out on the sidewalk

00:57.903 --> 01:00.308
having a screaming match
with Marty Dustin.

01:00.310 --> 01:02.340
Well, it wouldn't be
the first time.

01:02.342 --> 01:05.748
Another celebrity chef
I should know?

01:05.750 --> 01:08.383
Brent was Marty's mentor
on the show.

01:08.385 --> 01:10.120
They almost strangled
each other on live TV

01:10.122 --> 01:11.425
during the season finale.

01:11.427 --> 01:13.626
And Brent was holding
a knife that night,

01:13.628 --> 01:15.563
although he said it was
'cause Marty threatened him.

01:15.565 --> 01:17.194
Hmm.

01:17.196 --> 01:19.634
And you were too starstruck
to give a damn.

01:19.636 --> 01:20.963
I guess you
could say that.

01:20.965 --> 01:22.836
Bet you Marty wasn't.

01:24.670 --> 01:26.805
(sighs)

01:29.344 --> 01:32.479
(siren wailing)

01:34.000 --> 01:40.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:46.603 --> 01:48.001
WOMAN:
No, and you hide me away

01:48.003 --> 01:49.737
like you're
embarrassed of me.

01:49.739 --> 01:51.401
(gasping)

01:51.403 --> 01:52.808
Ma'am, roll down the window?
Just hold on.

01:52.810 --> 01:55.138
If that's all I am to you,
then we're done!

01:55.140 --> 01:56.411
MAN: Honey...
Ma'am!

01:56.413 --> 01:57.380
Just...

01:57.382 --> 01:59.685
What?

01:59.687 --> 02:01.021
You been drinking
tonight?

02:01.023 --> 02:03.086
What makes you think that?

02:03.088 --> 02:05.021
I just saw you blow
through a red light.

02:05.023 --> 02:07.493
Fine, maybe I had
a glass of wine.

02:07.495 --> 02:09.526
Ma'am, please turn
off the ignition,

02:09.527 --> 02:10.798
step out of
the vehicle.

02:10.800 --> 02:12.833
(sighs) Officer, is this
really necessary?

02:12.835 --> 02:14.033
Sir, I'm not
talking to you.

02:14.035 --> 02:15.401
I understand,
but I could switch places

02:15.403 --> 02:16.738
and just drive
her home.

02:16.740 --> 02:17.770
That's not how this works.

02:17.772 --> 02:19.338
Ma'am, step out of the vehicle.

02:19.340 --> 02:21.779
Do you not know
who he is?

02:21.781 --> 02:23.347
Jess, Jess...

02:23.349 --> 02:26.219
He's the majority speaker
for the state senate.

02:26.221 --> 02:27.147
How nice for him.

02:27.149 --> 02:28.451
I said step out
of the vehicle.

02:28.453 --> 02:30.683
Do we have
to do this, son?

02:30.685 --> 02:32.419
OFFICER 2:
Sir?

02:33.262 --> 02:34.525
Get back in the car,

02:34.527 --> 02:36.165
or I'm taking you both in
right now.

02:36.167 --> 02:37.566
She's right.

02:37.568 --> 02:39.334
I am Senator
Ted McCreary.

02:39.336 --> 02:42.036
Then you should know
that driving while intoxicated

02:42.038 --> 02:43.603
is illegal
in this state, Senator.

02:43.605 --> 02:46.035
Just do me a favor--
look at this...

02:46.037 --> 02:48.308
Stop right there! Take your hand
out of your pocket now!

02:48.310 --> 02:51.141
There, just look
at this card.

02:51.143 --> 02:55.151
This has the cell phone number
of Commissioner Reagan.

02:56.017 --> 02:58.383
Just call him.

02:58.385 --> 03:01.159
Trust me, you want
to make this call.

03:05.624 --> 03:09.565
Wait, he got mad at you because
you arrested him at work?

03:09.567 --> 03:11.900
After he robbed his
coworker at gunpoint.

03:11.902 --> 03:14.331
Said I was making him look
bad in front of the boss.

03:14.333 --> 03:15.963
(laughs)

03:15.965 --> 03:18.338
See what happens
when we take a day off?

03:18.340 --> 03:19.665
Weird things happen.

03:19.667 --> 03:21.833
Speaking of.

03:21.835 --> 03:24.008
What are they
all looking at?

03:25.842 --> 03:28.343
Something on their phones.

03:30.448 --> 03:34.810
So people ignore each other,
like, in big groups now?

03:34.812 --> 03:36.242
(chuckles)

03:45.985 --> 03:48.183
(cell phones beeping)

03:59.232 --> 04:00.631
Hey!

04:02.073 --> 04:03.968
Hey!

04:03.970 --> 04:05.870
JANKO:
Hey, are you okay?

04:05.872 --> 04:07.237
Are you okay?

04:07.239 --> 04:08.237
What?

04:08.239 --> 04:10.172
Talk to me. What's your name?

04:10.174 --> 04:11.970
Were you with any
of these people?

04:11.972 --> 04:14.671
Jamie.

04:15.810 --> 04:17.112
Hey, how did
you get here?

04:17.113 --> 04:19.406
How'd you get here?
Talk to me, talk to me.

04:19.409 --> 04:21.446
12 George to central,
requesting a bus.

04:21.447 --> 04:23.477
Washington Square Park,
underneath the arch.

04:23.479 --> 04:25.012
Possible O.D.

